{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"CORRECTION (harness bug fixed): the 'finder criteria mismatch' was a HARNESS artifact — I counted criteria only from schema-tagged calls; bespoke's finder records carried schema=None. Counting from ALL finder-role calls: criteria are FULL PARITY — all 25 criteria identical on both paths, same models (haiku), same call-modes (1-shot+agent). Coach: full parity (1 call each, plan supplied both, instructions match). Bug-exempt: full parity (0 LLM calls both).\n\nThe ONLY remaining difference is VERIFY BATCHING: bespoke pass2_verify chunks findings by 12 (3 calls [12,12,1] for 25 findings); the workflow issues ONE aggregate verify call ([25]). This is DESIGN-INTENDED — the epic AC specifies 'aggregate prompt verify (ONE call)', and the B4 parity harness already pins verify ROLE+call-mode (not batch count). Same prompt (plan-review-verifier), same findings SET, same call-mode; only the chunking differs. So the {{plan}}+instructions fix achieves the intended parity. Pending user call: accept the design-intended single-aggregate verify, or replicate bespoke's batch-by-12 in the workflow."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782515265134000001,"uuid":"dbe859a0-582c-4676-a9bf-0b6e479ba951"}